This is really hard for me to say but I just have to say it.

I saw a black Burberry trench coat the other day and I felt that I was very drawn to it even though I couldn’t afford it. I thought, “That’s weird, I know I can’t afford this, and yet I want it so badly. What’s wrong with me.”

And that’s when I realized. I identify as rich.
My whole life I’ve been living a life that is not mine as an upper-middle class person. But inside I have been rich this whole time, and I haven’t been able to live my life honestly.

I’m a rich person and I like luxurious things, yet I’ve been stuck in this non-rich person’s body. So I’m asking for help. I want this Burberry trench coat, and I feel like it will be the first step to help me live my authentic life as a rich person.

And you might think, “Why would I help you take steps to live your life as a rich person and be your true self when there are more severe things happening in the world?

That’s a great point.

If you feel it in your heart to help me take that first step to living as an openly rich person, please, help me get this coat. Thank you

Posting this to show growth. I can barely watch this because it’s so cringey, but you’ve got to be able to look at yourself and acknowledge your past. I had just finished a weekend of shows and there was a 2nd show on Sunday with headliner Shawty, and I asked if I could do time on it, and as you can see, it’s not like I even did bad, but I just feel so hacky and pandery watching this. I had just been on TV. I thought I was cool. I’m being so loud and awkward and ugh, it’s brutal. Unfortunately a couple of those jokes I do still pull out 😂 but I think I’ve come a long way from this over the last 8 years. Also, the last girl had just been booed off stage, so this was really my “I’m not scared of you” Bernie Mac moment 😂

A big part of the reason I visited Tampa was to be part of my friend Steve Miller’s benefit show. He’s sick and he lost his job so the community came together and raised money for him and I even got to perform with him on a second show later in the week. Shoutout to @sidesplitterstampa and @commodorecomedy. It was great to see so many friends come together to help another friend ❤️ if you ever see a flyer with Steve Miller‘s name on it, go to the show! You will not be disappointed

Literal bag chaser 👜 Honestly I don’t really like asking questions like this because I think it’s cheap and hacky but I know it’s sensational so every now and then I can’t help but slip one in because I know the internet likes it and sometimes it’s great. Anyways, this is a very powerful lesson on manifestation and how you can speak things into existence ✨😂

New year, new you(tube)! I started another YouTube channel because my first one I’ve had for 18 years and posted 1000 videos and have less than 3k subscribers so it’s just not working out 😂 Anyways, I’ll be posting longer stand up videos on the new channel so if you’re interested in that go follow me on Youtube at John Jacobs Comedian. 
One time a kid DM’d me and said “Hey I’m a fan you need a YouTube I’ll help you, you would be great on there.” And I responded that I’ve had a channel for a long time with a million videos, I sent it to him, then he ghosted me 😂 Anyways new year, new channel, and most importantly, new thumbnails because that’s apparently what drives stand up comedy. Good thumbnails. 🖼️ 
I just put out a 36 minute set on the channel so go watch it and let me know what you think 🙏 Working on cutting up this 2 1/2 hour set from the Improv which will be out soon.
(Also, I’ve been staying in London again my American number is off, so just message me on here or on WhatsApp)
